Hi,

finally starting work on the re-visting stuff:

Is there are reason why stuff in the FrontierMarker is package 
access only. I'm setting up my new Frontier in a new package 
and I've copy and pasted  Frontier.java in as a starting point
and of course it needs all the FrontierMarker stuff and can't 
see it because its no longer in the same package. 

I don't know enough about the codebase to start hacking at it 
right now so I'm just going to copy it as well. but i guess that 
there should be access methods for these protected memebers so
that writing a new frontier in a new package is do-able

cheers 

mark
